{{IPAfont|⟨kutu⟩}}: *{{IPAchar|/kutu/}} → {{IPAchar|/kut͡su/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=くつ|-}}. Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' poetry compilation, completed circa 759.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Ultimate derivation unclear. Some Japanese sources suggest a borrowing from Korean {{ko-l|구두||shoes}}, but then some Korean sources suggest that the Korean term was borrowed from Japanese {{lang|ja|靴}} (''kutsu'', “shoes”).

{{ja-noun|くつ}}

# [[footwear]], [[footgear]]: a [[shoe]], (a [[pair]] of) [[shoes]]
#* {{RQ:Manyoshu|14|3399}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man14Yo.html#3399 here]:
#*: {{lang|ja|信濃道者 伊麻能波里美知 可里婆祢尓 安思布麻之<奈牟> 久都波氣和我世}}
#*: {{ja-usex|信%濃%道 は 　今の墾り道 　刈りばね に 　足 踏ましなむ 　'''沓'''はけ我が背|しな%ぬ%ぢ は 　いま の はりみち 　かりばね に 　あし ふましなむ 　'''くつ''' はけ わがせ|the Shinano road has just been opened; wear '''shoes''', my brother / my dear, so you do not step on the brush stubble [in your bare feet]}}

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|靴%下|くつ%した}}: [[sock]]
* {{ja-r|靴%擦れ|くつ%ずれ}}: literally “[[shoe]] [[rubbing]]”: a [[blister]] on one's [[foot]] due to [[ill-fitting]] [[shoe]]s
{{der-mid}}
* {{ja-r|長%靴|なが%ぐつ}}: [[boot]]
